events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — The Houston Rockets lost their team-record 20th straight game, falling to the Oklahoma City Thunder 114-112 Sunday when John Wall missed two shots in the final 10 seconds.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets lose team-record 20th straight game, fall to Thunder

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram and Zion Williamson each scored 30 points and the New Orleans Pelicans overcame another triple-double by Nikola Jokic to beat the Denver Nuggets 113-108 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram, Williamson score 30, Pelicans beat Nuggets 113-108

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 34 points, including a career-high 10 3-pointers, and Jayson Tatum added 23 on Sunday to help the Boston Celtics beat the Orlando Magic 112-96 and snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown (34 pts, 10 3s) leads Celtics past Magic 112-96

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 28 points and James Harden had 26 to lead the Brooklyn Nets to a 113-106 victory over the Washington Wizards on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving, Harden help Nets beat Wizards in Griffin's debut

headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 23 of his 36 points in the second half, Jarrett Allen had 17 points and 15 rebounds and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat Toronto 116-105 on Sunday night, handing the Raptors their eighth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton scores 36, Cavs hand Raptors eighth straight loss

headlines.description: — Laurie Markkanen had 16 points and eight rebounds and the Chicago Bulls used a strong defensive performance for a 100-86 win over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen, solid defense lead Bulls over Pistons 100-86

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris made two free throws with 5.3 seconds left in overtime and the Philadelphia 76ers ran their winning streak against the New York Knicks to 15 games with a 101-100 victory Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers escape Knicks behind Harris' 2 late free throws in OT

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Devin Booker and Deandre Ayton both had 26 points, Chris Paul had a triple-double with 11 points, 13 assists and 10 rebounds and the Phoenix Suns beat the LeBron-less Los Angeles Lakers 111-94 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns roll past LeBron-less Lakers for 111-94 win

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 37 points in three quarters, leading the Dallas Mavericks to a 132-92 rout of the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 37, Mavericks rout Trail Blazers 132-92
